Sambatra ny olona izay tsy mandeha eo amin' ny fisainan' ny ratsy fanahy , ary tsy mijanona eo amin' ny lalana falehan' ny mpanota , ary tsy mipetraka eo amin' ny fipetrahan' ny mpaniratsira ; ||| How blessed is the one who does not follow the advice of the wicked , or stand in the pathway with sinners , or sit in the assembly of scoffers !
Fa ny lalàn' i Jehovah no sitrany ; eny ny lalàny no saintsaininy andro aman' alina . ||| Instead he finds pleasure in obeying the Lord 's commands ; he meditates on his commands day and night .
Dia tahaka ny hazo ambolena eo amoron' ny rano velona izy , izay mamoa amin' ny fotoany , ny raviny koa tsy mba malazo ; ary ny asany rehetra dia ataony lavorary avokoa . ||| He is like a tree planted by flowing streams ; it yields its fruit at the proper time , and its leaves never fall off . He succeeds in everything he attempts .
Fa tsy mba toy izany ny ratsy fanahy fa toy ny akofa aelin' ny rivotra izy . ||| Not so with the wicked ! Instead they are like wind @-@ driven chaff .
Ary noho izany ny ratsy fanahy dia tsy hahajanona eo amin' ny fitsarana , na ny mpanota eo amin' ny fiangonan' ny marina . ||| For this reason the wicked can not withstand judgment , nor can sinners join the assembly of the godly .
Fa fantatr' i Jehovah ny lalan' ny marina , fa ny lalan' ny ratsy fanahy kosa dia mankany amin' ny fahaverezana . ||| Certainly the Lord guards the way of the godly , but the way of the wicked ends in destruction .
